{"PageNumber":15,"Angle":0,"RotatedAngle":0,"Height":1620,"Width":2880,"OriginHeight":0,"OriginWidth":0,"Elements":[{"Index":0,"Type":"title","Text":"#  Classic cipher: Vigenère cipher","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":216,"Y":308},"LeftTop":{"X":216,"Y":187},"RightBottom":{"X":1838,"Y":308},"RightTop":{"X":1838,"Y":187}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":1,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● It applies to blocks of length $m$","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":525},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":441},"RightBottom":{"X":1308,"Y":525},"RightTop":{"X":1308,"Y":441}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":2,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● A key in this cryptosystem is a sequence of m shift amounts, $(k_1, k_2, \\dots, k_m)$ using the modulo of the alphabet size (26 for English)","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":742},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":561},"RightBottom":{"X":2621,"Y":742},"RightTop":{"X":2621,"Y":561}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":3,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Given a block of $m$ characters of plaintext, we encrypt the block by cyclically shifting the first character by $k_1$, the second by $k_2$, the third by $k_3$, and so on","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":1044},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":775},"RightBottom":{"X":2627,"Y":1044},"RightTop":{"X":2627,"Y":775}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":4,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Thus, there are potentially m different substitutions for any given letter in the plaintext (depending on where in the plaintext the letter appears)","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":1343},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":1075},"RightBottom":{"X":2613,"Y":1343},"RightTop":{"X":2613,"Y":1075}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""},{"Index":5,"Type":"paragraph","Text":"● Decryption is done by performing the reverse shifts on each block of $m$ characters in the ciphertext","Level":0,"Polygon":{"LeftBottom":{"X":219,"Y":1552},"LeftTop":{"X":219,"Y":1379},"RightBottom":{"X":2601,"Y":1552},"RightTop":{"X":2601,"Y":1379}},"InsetImageName":"","Elements":null,"ImagePath":"","group_id":-1,"group_type":""}]}